## 9. Zustand Store Pattern

Every store follows this structure:

import { create } from 'zustand'
import { db } from '../lib/db'
import { regenerateConfig } from '../lib/configGen'
import { invoke } from '../lib/tauri'

Each store:
  - loads from SQLite on mount
  - mutations = store update + db.execute + regenerateConfig()
  - optimistic: update state first, rollback on error
  - exposes: data array, loading bool, load(), add(), update(), remove()

useServiceGroupStore also has:
  addUpstream(groupId, upstream)
  removeUpstream(upstreamId)
  refreshHealth()  -- pings all upstreams via invoke('check_upstream_health')

Health refresh runs every 30s via setInterval at module level.

