## 10. Config Generation (src/lib/configGen.ts)

Called after EVERY store mutation. Users never manually trigger it.

regenerateConfig():
  1. Read all stores (routes, groups, middleware, tls, settings)
  2. Call buildTraefikV3YAML() to produce YAML string
  3. invoke('write_config', { yaml, path })
  4. invoke('reload_proxy')

buildTraefikV3YAML() produces:

  Static config:
    entryPoints: web(:80) websecure(:443)
    certificatesResolvers if ACME mode
    forwardedHeaders.trustedIPs if Cloudflare mode (uses cloudflareIPs.ts ranges)
    api block if admin port set

  Dynamic config (providers.file):
    http.routers — one per enabled route
      rule: Host(`jellyfin.example.com`)
         or Host(`example.com`) && PathPrefix(`/api`)
      middlewares: [array of middleware ids]
      service: serviceGroupId
      tls.certResolver: "letsencrypt" if ACME

    http.services — one per service group
      loadBalancer.servers: [{ url: "http://192.168.1.10:8096" }, ...]
      loadBalancer.healthCheck: { path, interval, timeout }
      loadBalancer.passiveHealthCheck if enabled

    http.middlewares — one per enabled middleware with its config

    tls.certificates — manual cert entries if manual mode

