## 13. Coding Rules

1.  TypeScript strict mode, zero any types
2.  No raw config file editing in UI — path shown read-only in Settings only
3.  Auto-regenerate config after EVERY store mutation, no manual apply button
4.  Optimistic UI — update store immediately, rollback + show toast on Tauri error
5.  All invoke() calls wrapped in try/catch, user sees toast on error
6.  Max 200 lines per component, extract sub-components early
7.  No inline styles — Tailwind classes or CSS custom properties only
8.  Monospace class on ALL IP addresses, ports, paths, hostnames
9.  Accessible — labels on all inputs, modals trap focus and close on ESC
10. Health polling — setInterval in useServiceGroupStore, 30s, starts on mount
11. Log streaming — Tauri listen() only, never polling
12. Path strip preview — when strip toggle ON, always show:
      "example.com/api/users → backend receives GET /users"
13. Colour dot consistency — service group colour appears in:
      group card dot, routes table dot, dashboard health list dot
14. Status toggle in routes table — clicking ON/OFF immediately updates route.enabled
      and calls regenerateConfig() without opening the edit modal
15. "+ New group…" option in route modal service group dropdown — clicking it
      closes the route modal and opens the new service group modal, then returns

