## 16. High Availability (keepalived / VRRP)

Architecture:
  Domain DNS → Floating VIP 203.0.113.10
  Floating VIP held by ProxyGate A (primary) normally
  If A dies, keepalived on B claims VIP within ~1 second
  Domain stays up, users notice nothing

Both ProxyGate nodes run identical config (synced via rsync or shared NFS).
HA panel in Settings generates /etc/keepalived/keepalived.conf.
User provides: role, VIP, peer IP, network interface.
ProxyGate writes the keepalived config — user never edits it manually.
